               <t:note>
                  <t:date type="foundation" from="1737" to="1738">1737/'38</t:date>
                  <t:ab type="history">The church of Nārgā Śǝllāse is located on the islet of
                        <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC4969Narga">Nārgā</t:placeName>, east of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2522Daq">Daq</t:placeName> island in the middle of lake <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5888Tana">Ṭānā</t:placeName>. It was founded in <t:date from="1737" to="1738">1737/'38</t:date> by <t:roleName type="title">ʾǝtege</t:roleName>
                     <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2682BerhanM">Mǝntǝwwāb</t:persName> and this event is described
                     in the <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2624ZenaNa">Zenā Nārgā</t:ref>. The
                     construction of the entire complex took up to <t:date when="1750">1750</t:date> and
                     the church was endowed by <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2682BerhanM">Mǝntǝwwāb</t:persName>
                     and her son <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5617IyasuII">ʾIyāsu II</t:persName> with books and
                     liturgical objects. The church was partially restored in the <t:date from="1950" to="1960">1950s</t:date> under <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5226haylase">Ḫāyla Śǝllāse
                        I</t:persName>.</t:ab>
                  <t:ab type="description">Nārgā Śǝllāse is a round centrally-planned church of stones
                     and lime located at the centre of a compound. The church was adorned with
                     engravings on wood and stone and with murals on the external walls. Some parts
                     of the church were later repainted.</t:ab>
               </t:note>
